osition":0},"title":"Hadith on Faith: Example of believers who endure trials","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 28, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe parable of the believer is a fresh plant, the leaves of which rustle in whatever direction the wind takes them, but when the winds calm down, it returns to its balance. Such is the parable\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25915,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/02\/07\/question-wish-not-asked\/","url_meta":{"origin":10004,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Miracles: Question the Prophet wished he had not asked","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 7, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cI asked my Lord a question I wish I had not asked. I said: O Lord, there were messengers before me, among them those for whom you subordinated the wind and among them those who resurrected\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6606,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/18\/sahaba-evil-wind\/","url_meta":{"origin":10004,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Gheebah: Companions smell evil wind of backbiting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: We were with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, when we detected a foul odor carried by the wind. The Prophet said, \u201cDo you know what this wind is? It is the smell of those who backbite the believers.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 14784 Grade:\u00a0Hasan\u00a0(fair)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32180,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/15\/do-not-curse-wind\/","url_meta":{"origin":10004,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Weather: Do not curse wind directed by Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: A man cursed the wind in front of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. The Prophet said, \u201cDo not curse the wind, for it only acts as it was commanded. Verily, whoever curses anything that does not deserve it, the curse will backfire against him.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18465,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/08\/dua-entering-town\/","url_meta":{"origin":10004,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet\u2019s supplication for entering a city","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 8, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Suhayb reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, intended to enter a town, he would say, \u201cO Allah, Lord of the seven heavens and what they overshadow, Lord of the seven earths and what they cover, Lord of the devils and who they lead astra